The paper discusses the performance analysis of Estimation of Distribution Algorithms (EDAs), which are commonly used in optimization problems in various fields including machine learning, artificial intelligence, and operations research. The paper specifically focuses on the Univariate Marginal Distribution Algorithm (UMDA) and provides upper bounds on the expected optimization time for various problems. This work involves the use of probabilistic models, stochastic heuristics, and population-based algorithms, which are all relevant to the sub-fields of neural networks (cs.NE), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT).
